FAW, Isuzu Plan Plants in South Africa, Bus. Day Says

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-10-14T05:04:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/faw-isuzu-plan-plants-in-south-africa-bus-day-says-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling in headline.)  FAW Car Co. of China plans to build
a $100 million truck and car plant at Coega in  South Africa 
while  Isuzu Motors Ltd. (7202)  may build an assembly plant at the site,
Johannesburg’s Business Day newspaper reported, citing the
companies.  FAW’s plant may open next year and produce 5,000 vehicles
annually with an eventual capacity of 30,000 units planned, the
newspaper said, citing Richard Leiter, the managing director of
the country’s South African unit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  